---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { CONTACT_EMAIL, COMPANY_NAME } from "../config";

const lastUpdated = "27 April 2026";
---

<Layout title={`Privacy — ${COMPANY_NAME}`} path="/privacy">
  <SiteNav variant="full" />

  <main
    class="px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16 pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32"
    style="background: var(--color-bg);"
  >
    <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h1
        class="font-serif leading-[1.02] tracking-tight"
        style="
          color: var(--color-ink);
          font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.75rem);
        "
      >
        A note on data and privacy.
      </h1>

      <p
        class="mt-6 md:mt-8 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed"
        style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);"
      >
        We keep this short and direct. {COMPANY_NAME} collects very little.
        What we do collect, we use carefully.
      </p>

      <p
        class="mt-3 text-sm"
        style="color: var(--color-ink-subtle);"
      >
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-14 space-y-12 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-ink);">

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            What we collect
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            When you submit a brief through the form on this site, we collect
            what you give us — typically your name, your email, your company,
            and the details of your campaign brief. Nothing else. We don't run
            analytics on this site, we don't set advertising cookies, and we
            don't track you across the web.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            Where it goes
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            Three services touch your data, all based in the United States:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-5 space-y-4 list-disc pl-5" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            <li>
              <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Formspree</strong> receives
              the intake form and forwards the contents to our inbox. Their
              policy lives at
              <a
                href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy"
                class="underline underline-offset-2"
                style="color: var(--color-accent);"
              >formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Google Workspace</strong>
              hosts our email, including any reply thread that grows from your
              brief.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Google Fonts</strong> loads
              two typefaces from Google's CDN when you visit, which briefly
              exposes your IP address to Google. We are aware of the concerns
              around this and plan to self-host the fonts in a future deploy.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-5" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            We don't share your data with anyone outside these processors.
            We don't sell it. We don't pass it to creators unless you've
            explicitly asked us to.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            Why we are allowed to hold it
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            Under GDPR, we rely on two legal bases. When you send us a brief,
            we process your data to take steps toward a possible contract
            (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR). For ongoing communication and record-keeping
            after that, we rely on our legitimate interest in running the
            business (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR), balanced against your right to
            object at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            How long we keep it
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            If we work together, we hold your data for the length of the
            engagement plus the period required by applicable tax and
            contracting law (typically up to seven years for invoicing
            records).
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            If we don't work together — say you submit a brief and we never
            proceed — we hold what you sent for twelve months and then delete
            it. The window exists so that if you come back later, we still
            have the context.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            Your rights
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            Under GDPR you can ask us to:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            <li>Show you what we have on you</li>
            <li>Correct anything that is wrong</li>
            <li>Delete it</li>
            <li>Export it so you can take it elsewhere</li>
            <li>Stop processing it</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-5" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            Send any of these requests to
            <a
              href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}
              class="underline underline-offset-2"
              style="color: var(--color-accent);"
            >{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. We act on them within thirty days. If you
            think we have handled your data poorly, you can also lodge a
            complaint with your local supervisory authority.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="font-serif tracking-tight"
            style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.15;"
          >
            Contact
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);">
            {COMPANY_NAME} is operated from the United States. For any privacy
            question, write to
            <a
              href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}
              class="underline underline-offset-2"
              style="color: var(--color-accent);"
            >{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
